title: John Singer Sargent Boxed Note Cards
description:
Cards developed from John Singer Sargent’s The Fountain, Villa Torlonia, Frascati, Italy, 1914, and An Artist at His Easel, 1914, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Ideal for sending a quick note or announcement.

  • Dimensions: Card size: 3.5 x 4.874 in, Box size: 4.182 x 5.5 in.
  • Set of 20 cards and 21 envelopes
  • Box lid has a magnetic closure
